snippet.textDisplay: Sweet undercurrents of psychedelic rock reminiscent of classic Pink Floyd light the fuse to an extravagant rock number. So much is happening, it's like a box of fireworks all going off at once. I love the erratic incursions from the string section which remind me of a punky version of the Electric Light Orchestra. Traditional percussion brings a welcome intermission behind Musarrat Nazir's voice for the middle section of the song before the whole track pulls together for a compelling climax. This one may need a few listens to settle in to, it throws up some challenges but it really works.
snippet.textOriginal: Sweet undercurrents of psychedelic rock reminiscent of classic Pink Floyd light the fuse to an extravagant rock number.
